Sentencas: All-thin film solid oxide cells (ATF-SOCs) have exhibited exceptional performance at a wide range of operating conditions.
Titulo: High performance, enhanced structural stability of co-sputtered nanocomposite anode with neutral stress state for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: However, despite the significant attention given to demonstrating the performance of ATF-SOCs, the correlation between their high performance and structural stability in comparison to sputtered metal or conventional sintered electrodes remains an area of active research.
Titulo: High performance, enhanced structural stability of co-sputtered nanocomposite anode with neutral stress state for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This study demonstrates high performance and enhanced thermal stability of co-sputtered nanocomposite Ni-Gd doped ceria (GDC) anode with extremely low contents of GDC.
Titulo: High performance, enhanced structural stability of co-sputtered nanocomposite anode with neutral stress state for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: By tailoring the nanostructure of co -sputtered Ni-GDC anode with extremely low GDC contents, the electrochemical performance of TF-SOFCs increased more than 50% (749 mWcm-2 @ 500 degrees C) compared to the high-performance nano -structured Ni anode.
Titulo: High performance, enhanced structural stability of co-sputtered nanocomposite anode with neutral stress state for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This unconventional optimization of GDC composition ratio in co-sputtered Ni-GDC anode is attributed to the residual stress formed in thin film nanostructure.
Titulo: High performance, enhanced structural stability of co-sputtered nanocomposite anode with neutral stress state for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The analysis of residual stress has revealed that the increase in doped ceria contents in co-sputtered Ni-GDC increases the tensile stress in the thin film structure, causing the formation of cracks in the Ni-GDC anode with high ceria content in reducing environment.
Titulo: High performance, enhanced structural stability of co-sputtered nanocomposite anode with neutral stress state for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: By controlling the GDC composition during the co-sputtering process, a neutral stress state was achieved in the co-sputtered nanocomposite, resulting in significantly enhanced per-formance and stability.(c) 2023
Titulo: High performance, enhanced structural stability of co-sputtered nanocomposite anode with neutral stress state for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
